# CaptionDB Backend Engineering Contract

## Purpose

This document defines the mandatory backend engineering standards for CaptionDB.

The backend is the orchestration engine of the application.

Its responsibility is to coordinate services, validate requests, manage application state, and expose APIs.

Business logic belongs inside services.

The backend must remain independent of frontend implementation details.

---

# Backend Philosophy

The backend is the heart of CaptionDB.

It is not merely an API.

It is responsible for:

- orchestration
- business logic
- validation
- AI pipeline coordination
- configuration
- observability
- error handling

The backend should remain reusable even if the frontend changes completely.

---

# Technology Stack

Mandatory stack:

- Python 3.12+
- FastAPI
- Pydantic v2
- Uvicorn
- HTTPX
- Loguru or standard logging
- PyYAML
- python-dotenv

Avoid unnecessary dependencies.

Every dependency must have a clear justification.

---

# Application Structure

The backend should follow this structure.

backend/

app/

api/

core/

config/

models/

schemas/

services/

repositories/

workers/

plugins/

cache/

utils/

tests/

scripts/

Every directory has one responsibility.

Never place unrelated code together.

---

# FastAPI Usage

FastAPI is the application backbone.

Use FastAPI for:

- dependency injection
- configuration
- lifecycle management
- request validation
- response serialization

Avoid placing business logic inside routes.

---

# Route Responsibilities

Routes should only:

Receive request

↓

Validate input

↓

Call service

↓

Return response

Routes must never:

Call Fireworks directly

Perform OCR

Run AI inference

Contain business logic

Access databases directly

---

# Service Layer

All business logic belongs inside services.

Examples

VideoService

CaptionService

SceneService

ExportService

FireworksService

OCRService

PromptService

JudgeService

MemoryService

Services should communicate through interfaces whenever practical.

---

# Repository Layer

Use repositories only when persistent storage is introduced.

Do not create repositories without a clear need.

Repositories should abstract storage implementation.

Never expose storage implementation to services.

---

# Dependency Injection

All shared services must be injected.

Never instantiate services directly inside routes.

Prefer constructor injection.

Use FastAPI Depends where appropriate.

---

# Configuration

Every configurable value must come from:

Environment variables

Configuration files

Settings objects

Never hardcode:

URLs

API keys

Timeouts

Model IDs

Frame counts

Retry limits

Prompt names

Export paths

Feature flags

---

# Request Validation

Every request must be validated.

Validate:

JSON

Files

Headers

Parameters

Body

Never trust client input.

Reject invalid input immediately.

---

# Response Models

Every endpoint must return typed response models.

Never return anonymous dictionaries.

Responses should be predictable and documented.

---

# Exception Handling

Never expose raw exceptions.

Use custom exceptions.

Centralize exception handling.

Return consistent error responses.

Unexpected failures must be logged.

---

# Global Exception Handler

Implement centralized exception handlers.

Convert internal exceptions into safe API responses.

Never expose stack traces.

Never expose internal implementation.

---

# Logging

Every request should log:

Request ID

Execution time

Status

Warnings

Errors

Retry attempts

Do not log sensitive information.

---

# Correlation IDs

Every incoming request should receive a unique request identifier.

All logs generated during that request should include the same identifier.

This simplifies debugging.

---

# Middleware

Use middleware only when justified.

Examples:

Logging

Request timing

Correlation IDs

Security headers

Compression

Avoid unnecessary middleware.

---

# Background Tasks

Long-running work should not block request processing.

Use:

Background tasks

Worker queues

Async processing

where appropriate.

---

# API Versioning

Design APIs to support future versions.

Prefer:

/api/v1/

instead of

/api/

Future versions should coexist.

---

# Health Endpoint

Implement:

/health

Return:

application status

dependency status

configuration status

version

uptime

No sensitive information.

---

# Readiness Endpoint

Implement:

/ready

Verify:

configuration

required services

Fireworks connectivity (when appropriate)

model availability

Return readiness status.

---

# Metrics Endpoint

Implement metrics support.

Capture:

request count

request latency

error count

processing duration

Fireworks latency

OCR latency

scene detection duration

caption generation duration

cache hit ratio

---

# Timeout Policy

Every external request must define a timeout.

Never rely on infinite waits.

Use configurable timeout values.

---

# Retry Policy

Retry only transient failures.

Examples:

network timeout

temporary service unavailable

rate limit

Use exponential backoff.

Never retry validation failures.

---

# Async Guidelines

Network operations should use asynchronous clients.

CPU-intensive work should not block the event loop.

Use appropriate execution strategies.

Avoid unnecessary async usage.

---

# File Uploads

Validate:

extension

MIME type

size

duration

Reject unsupported files immediately.

Never trust file names.

Generate internal file identifiers.

---

# Temporary Files

Store temporary files in controlled locations.

Automatically clean them after processing.

Never leave temporary files behind.

---

# Caching

Cache only expensive computations.

Examples:

scene detection

OCR

embeddings

video metadata

Prompt templates

Do not cache mutable business state.

---

# Feature Flags

Optional functionality must be controlled through configuration.

Never comment out code to disable features.

Examples:

OCR

Audio

Memory

Judge

Experimental prompts

---

# Interfaces

External integrations must remain behind interfaces.

Never couple application logic directly to:

Fireworks SDK

OCR engine

Scene detector

Storage provider

Export engine

All integrations must be replaceable.

---

# Observability

Every major operation should expose:

execution duration

resource usage

retry count

failure reason

success status

This information should support production debugging.

---

# Security

Validate every request.

Sanitize every filename.

Normalize every path.

Protect every endpoint from malformed input.

Never expose secrets.

Never trust external systems.

---

# Documentation

Every endpoint must include:

summary

description

response model

error responses

tags

FastAPI OpenAPI documentation should remain complete.

---

# Testing

Every service should support isolated testing.

Mock external dependencies.

Avoid network calls during unit tests.

Write integration tests separately.

---

# Self Review Checklist

Before completing backend implementation verify:

✓ Thin routes

✓ Business logic in services

✓ Configuration driven

✓ Dependency injection used

✓ Typed models

✓ Structured logging

✓ Custom exceptions

✓ Request validation

✓ Response models

✓ Async used correctly

✓ Security reviewed

✓ Tests added

✓ Documentation updated

If any item fails, revise the implementation before completion.

---

End of Backend Engineering Contract.
